00:09:00.106 --> 00:09:01.874 line:95%,end
My daughter is a 10-year-old little girl.

00:09:01.941 --> 00:09:05.044 line:95%,end
And when you have 40-year-old women
who will stop at nothing

00:09:05.111 --> 00:09:07.480 line:95%,end
to tear her down
because of a dance, I'm sorry,

00:09:07.547 --> 00:09:09.749 line:95%,end
I'm going to step in.
And I'm not going to take it.

00:09:09.815 --> 00:09:12.852 line:95%,end
You are a (bleep) troublemaker,
and you're a bitch!

00:09:12.919 --> 00:09:15.421 line:95%,end
I'm not the liar of the group. Sorry.

00:09:15.488 --> 00:09:17.823 line:95%,end
Just like you lied
about my daughter cheating.

00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:19.959 line:95%,end
I didn't lie! You told her you cheated!

00:09:20.026 --> 00:09:21.928 line:95%,end
-I did not!
-You told her that!

00:09:21.994 --> 00:09:23.195 line:95%,end
I did not!

00:09:23.262 --> 00:09:25.298 line:95%,end
I'm not (bleep) doing this
anymore about this.

00:09:25.364 --> 00:09:27.033 line:95%,end
Who's the liar in this group?

00:09:27.099 --> 00:09:28.834 line:95%,end
-Who lies all the time? You.
-Okay. Yeah.

00:09:28.901 --> 00:09:31.003 line:95%,end
Who had an affair with her boss?

00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:33.706 line:95%,end
Who is living with a man
who is still married?

00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:35.942 line:95%,end
That's it.

00:09:36.008 --> 00:09:38.611 line:95%,end
-I did not have an affair with my boss!
-CHRISTI: Yes, you did!

00:09:38.678 --> 00:09:41.113 line:95%,end
(bleep) you. I did not (bleep) bitch!

00:09:41.180 --> 00:09:43.482 line:95%,end
(bleep) There, I said it.

00:09:43.549 --> 00:09:44.517 line:95%,end
There's a new word.

00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:46.285 line:95%,end
We haven't used that one, yet.

00:09:46.352 --> 00:09:49.121 line:95%,end
JILL: Well, I feel--I feel badly for her

00:09:49.188 --> 00:09:51.691 line:95%,end
because she was very upset.

00:09:51.757 --> 00:09:55.828 line:95%,end
And I think she does things,
you guys, to get along.

00:09:55.895 --> 00:09:58.531 line:95%,end
<i>She wants to be on the team</i>
<i>and be a team player.</i>

00:09:58.598 --> 00:10:00.433 line:95%,end
<i>And, you know, I don't know.</i>

00:10:00.499 --> 00:10:02.134 line:95%,end
-HOLLY: All I will say--
-JILL: I don't know why she does

00:10:02.201 --> 00:10:03.336 line:95%,end
-what she does.
-All I will say is this.

00:10:03.402 --> 00:10:06.472 line:95%,end
Melissa is an incredibly smart woman.

00:10:06.539 --> 00:10:08.174 line:95%,end
So she knows exactly what she's doing...

00:10:08.240 --> 00:10:09.342 line:95%,end
-CHRISTI: Exactly.
-JILL: ...as she does it...

00:10:09.408 --> 00:10:11.077 line:95%,end
-CHRISTI: Yes.
-JILL: ...while she's doing it.

00:10:11.143 --> 00:10:13.012 line:95%,end
They're talking about you.

00:10:13.079 --> 00:10:14.413 line:95%,end
I know Mackenzie.

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:18.117 line:95%,end
-I know, they're horrible.
-(crying)

00:10:18.184 --> 00:10:20.720 line:95%,end
Why do they do this to you?

00:10:20.786 --> 00:10:23.155 line:95%,end
I don't want you to leave.

00:10:23.222 --> 00:10:25.925 line:95%,end
Like, you think you're one step ahead,
she's four steps ahead of you.

00:10:25.992 --> 00:10:28.027 line:95%,end
Do not underestimate Melissa.


00:10:30.963 --> 00:10:33.966 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:10:35.067 --> 00:10:37.803 line:5%,start
JILL: Okay. So where is Melissa?

00:10:37.870 --> 00:10:39.739 line:95%,end
She's part of this team.
She needs to be here.

00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:43.175 line:95%,end
<i>It's the next day,</i>
<i>and everybody is there but Melissa.</i>

00:10:43.242 --> 00:10:46.112 line:5%,start
Kendall's not officially in the group.

00:10:46.178 --> 00:10:49.015 line:5%,start
So with Melissa out of the picture,

00:10:49.081 --> 00:10:52.151 line:95%,end
this just opens up doors for Kendall.

00:10:52.218 --> 00:10:55.187 line:95%,end
ABBY: Hey, girls.
Come on, come on, come on.

00:10:55.254 --> 00:10:56.555 line:95%,end
Is that your lantern?

00:10:57.256 --> 00:11:00.092 line:95%,end
Everything else had glass
and it's too heavy.

00:11:00.159 --> 00:11:01.460 line:95%,end
I don't know if this is going to work.

00:11:01.527 --> 00:11:04.664 line:95%,end
I'm just afraid it's too big and high.

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:06.632 line:95%,end
If not, we can look for a smaller one.

00:11:06.699 --> 00:11:08.234 line:95%,end
Okay. Where is Melissa?

00:11:08.300 --> 00:11:10.169 line:95%,end
Girls, where's Maddie?

00:11:10.236 --> 00:11:11.737 line:95%,end
We don't know.

00:11:11.804 --> 00:11:13.205 line:95%,end
All right. Let me go find out.

00:11:13.272 --> 00:11:15.441 line:95%,end
Because she would not
show up without calling.

00:11:15.508 --> 00:11:17.543 line:95%,end
Okay. Bring this in
when it's time for your solo.

00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:18.444 line:95%,end
-All right?
-Yes.

00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:20.079 line:95%,end
And let me see what's going on.

00:11:20.146 --> 00:11:24.316 line:5%,start
I'm starting rehearsal--
no Melissa, no kids.

00:11:24.383 --> 00:11:25.885 line:95%,end
I wonder if she'll be punished.

00:11:25.951 --> 00:11:27.319 line:95%,end
Doubt it.

00:11:27.386 --> 00:11:30.389 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:11:30.456 --> 00:11:32.391 line:5%,start
CATHY: Hey, guys, come on in. Apples!

00:11:33.459 --> 00:11:37.430 line:95%,end
So, everybody,
I have some top secret news.

00:11:37.496 --> 00:11:39.832 line:95%,end
We are going to Starbound in Myrtle Beach.

00:11:39.899 --> 00:11:42.501 line:95%,end
So we need to get busy
with new choreography.

00:11:42.568 --> 00:11:45.504 line:5%,start
The last time that I saw
the Abby Lee Dance Company

00:11:45.571 --> 00:11:48.641 line:95%,end
at a competition,
they were not very nice to me.

00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:50.943 line:95%,end
ABBY: I'm in Ohio. I'm on your turf.

00:11:51.010 --> 00:11:52.878 line:95%,end
Not even a cocktail party
the night before?

00:11:52.945 --> 00:11:54.113 line:95%,end
No dinner at your house?

00:11:54.180 --> 00:11:55.748 line:5%,start
We have the M&amp;M's back

00:11:55.815 --> 00:11:58.684 line:5%,start
-to help with choreography.
-(applause)

00:11:58.751 --> 00:12:01.187 line:95%,end
Mitchell and Michael are working with us.

00:12:01.253 --> 00:12:02.722 line:95%,end
And it's because they would like to see us

00:12:02.788 --> 00:12:04.557 line:95%,end
beat the Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:12:04.623 --> 00:12:06.459 line:95%,end
<i>The reason that I brought the M&amp;M's back</i>

00:12:06.525 --> 00:12:08.794 line:95%,end
is because the kids are really
reciprocating to them.

00:12:08.861 --> 00:12:10.596 line:95%,end
They love Mitchell and Michael.

00:12:10.663 --> 00:12:13.466 line:95%,end
<i>I think it's awesome.</i>
<i>I think it puts us on the edge.</i>

00:12:13.532 --> 00:12:15.434 line:95%,end
We need to really work hard this week

00:12:15.501 --> 00:12:20.940 line:95%,end
because Jill and Kendall
have hopped back to Abby's studio.

00:12:21.607 --> 00:12:23.075 line:95%,end
No surprise, of course.

00:12:23.142 --> 00:12:26.779 line:95%,end
Drazen, that's why you are going
to be dancing with us today,

00:12:26.846 --> 00:12:31.383 line:95%,end
because I wanted Justice
to have a male friend.

00:12:31.450 --> 00:12:35.688 line:95%,end
So I want Jill and Kendall going down.

00:12:35.755 --> 00:12:38.591 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:12:38.657 --> 00:12:40.559 line:95%,end
ABBY: Five, six, seven, go.

00:12:40.626 --> 00:12:43.262 line:5%,start
Ha! Ha! Ha!

00:12:43.329 --> 00:12:45.464 line:95%,end
Strong arms.
You're reaching for her, Brooke.

00:12:45.531 --> 00:12:47.133 line:95%,end
Reach out there! Boom!

00:12:47.199 --> 00:12:48.667 line:95%,end
<i>So I resume my rehearsal.</i>

00:12:48.734 --> 00:12:50.603 line:95%,end
I don't know what's going on
with Maddie and Melissa,

00:12:50.669 --> 00:12:52.805 line:95%,end
but they need to be here in rehearsal.

00:12:52.872 --> 00:12:55.941 line:95%,end
<i>You signed a contract.</i>
<i>You made a commitment to this team.</i>

00:12:56.008 --> 00:12:58.344 line:95%,end
I don't have time. I just don't.
I have to keep working.

00:12:58.410 --> 00:13:01.547 line:95%,end
Okay. Take it from the fan kick.
I want to hear your mouth.

00:13:01.614 --> 00:13:04.083 line:95%,end
One, two, three.

00:13:04.150 --> 00:13:06.519 line:95%,end
I must say, this is a first
for Melissa not to come.

00:13:06.585 --> 00:13:09.688 line:95%,end
JILL: I'm surprised that Abby
is even going to hold a class

00:13:09.755 --> 00:13:11.190 line:95%,end
without Mackenzie and Maddie.
What's going to happen?

00:13:11.257 --> 00:13:13.325 line:95%,end
Well, I'm sure she won't
put anyone in their spot.

00:13:13.392 --> 00:13:14.593 line:95%,end
-Well, that's my point.
-HOLLY: Oh.

00:13:14.660 --> 00:13:16.395 line:95%,end
-CHRISTI: (laughs)
-If my kid wasn't here,

00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:18.030 line:95%,end
someone would be replacing them.

00:13:18.097 --> 00:13:21.033 line:95%,end
<i>I think that Jill is just</i>
<i>loving life right now.</i>

00:13:21.100 --> 00:13:23.936 line:5%,start
Melissa is mad at us,
so she's not showing up for anything.

00:13:24.003 --> 00:13:26.071 line:95%,end
And my two kids are injured.

00:13:26.138 --> 00:13:29.341 line:95%,end
So she can just slither her way in
either with the moms

00:13:29.408 --> 00:13:30.543 line:95%,end
or the kids this week.

00:13:30.609 --> 00:13:32.711 line:95%,end
I guess she's not coming
because she doesn't want to

00:13:32.778 --> 00:13:33.846 line:95%,end
face the music, again.

00:13:33.913 --> 00:13:36.615 line:95%,end
Or maybe she didn't come today
because she can't be handle the truth.

00:13:36.682 --> 00:13:37.917 line:95%,end
-HOLLY: I can't believe she's not here.
-JILL: Well, or both.

00:13:37.983 --> 00:13:39.518 line:95%,end
Well, she knows it'll be
brought up, again.

00:13:40.853 --> 00:13:43.022 line:95%,end
CATHY: You have to bring it to the table.

00:13:43.088 --> 00:13:46.425 line:5%,start
And when you slam on this table,
whose face on this table?


00:13:46.492 --> 00:13:48.260 line:95%,end
-Jill.
-MICHAEL: Jill.

00:13:48.794 --> 00:13:49.628 line:95%,end
Okay?

00:13:49.695 --> 00:13:51.697 line:95%,end
CATHY: <i>The duo is called "The Promotion,"</i>

00:13:51.764 --> 00:13:56.869 line:95%,end
and they are supposed to be
looking like they're focused,

00:13:56.936 --> 00:13:58.504 line:95%,end
intense with each other.

00:13:58.571 --> 00:14:00.139 line:95%,end
They're both out for the competition.

00:14:00.206 --> 00:14:01.473 line:95%,end
We're struggling with that, though.

00:14:01.540 --> 00:14:07.446 line:95%,end
And one, two, go three,
go four, go five, go six, seven, eight.

00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:08.547 line:95%,end
Okay, stop.

00:14:08.614 --> 00:14:10.749 line:95%,end
But see how you have,
like, a smirk on your face?

00:14:10.816 --> 00:14:11.851 line:95%,end
-You're mean.
-CATHY: No smirking.

00:14:11.917 --> 00:14:14.954 line:95%,end
Justice finds it very difficult
to do anything

00:14:15.020 --> 00:14:18.958 line:95%,end
that presents him
in being a nasty kid-like.

00:14:19.024 --> 00:14:20.459 line:95%,end
So he's got to dig.

00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:21.927 line:95%,end
MITCHELL: Let's put Taylor up here.

00:14:21.994 --> 00:14:25.464 line:5%,start
-CATHY: Just play along with it, okay?
-And then you two go here.

00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:28.500 line:95%,end
-Let's switch and put Erica in the front.
-MITCHELL: Okay.

00:14:28.567 --> 00:14:31.737 line:95%,end
The group number is called
"My Hair Like This."

00:14:31.804 --> 00:14:34.540 line:95%,end
-Go, girls!
-(upbeat music playing)

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:40.746 line:95%,end
<i>I like the number</i>
<i>because it's very on the edge.</i>

00:14:40.813 --> 00:14:43.182 line:95%,end
<i>There's a lot of movement going on.</i>

00:14:43.249 --> 00:14:45.918 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:14:45.985 --> 00:14:47.853 line:95%,end
It's hot. It's a hot dance.

00:14:47.920 --> 00:14:49.688 line:95%,end
MITCHELL: One, two, three--

00:14:49.755 --> 00:14:51.257 line:95%,end
Work!

00:14:51.323 --> 00:14:53.225 line:95%,end
ABBY: I need to talk to my dance captain.

00:14:53.292 --> 00:14:54.593 line:95%,end
Come here.

00:14:55.227 --> 00:14:56.462 line:95%,end
You're down a dancer.

00:14:56.528 --> 00:14:59.064 line:95%,end
So I want you to go out,
get your cell phone,

00:14:59.131 --> 00:15:02.401 line:95%,end
call Maddie and tell her
to get her butt in here right now.

00:15:02.468 --> 00:15:05.838 line:5%,start
NIA: As dance captain,
I have to call Maddie

00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:10.009 line:5%,start
and tell her to come to the dance studio.

00:15:10.075 --> 00:15:12.144 line:95%,end
But I don't know how to get her here

00:15:12.211 --> 00:15:13.913 line:95%,end
because I'm not her mother.

00:15:13.979 --> 00:15:16.815 line:95%,end
Miss Abby really need you here right now.

00:15:16.882 --> 00:15:21.120 line:95%,end
Because I know that you are
one of the featured parts in the dance.

00:15:21.186 --> 00:15:24.924 line:95%,end
During the phone call,
Maddie says that her mother

00:15:24.990 --> 00:15:27.359 line:95%,end
won't let her come to the dance studio

00:15:27.426 --> 00:15:30.896 line:95%,end
because Melissa is always mad at the moms.

00:15:30.963 --> 00:15:32.865 line:95%,end
ABBY: Let's take it from the top,
straight through.

00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:37.002 line:95%,end
Remember, you guys are all as one.

00:15:37.069 --> 00:15:39.338 line:95%,end
You think alike. You stand alike.
You act alike.

00:15:39.405 --> 00:15:41.173 line:95%,end
Reach in.

00:15:41.240 --> 00:15:42.274 line:95%,end
Go!

00:15:42.341 --> 00:15:45.611 line:95%,end
Three and four--no.

00:15:45.678 --> 00:15:48.981 line:95%,end
You're on the outside,
then you, then Maddie.

00:15:49.048 --> 00:15:49.882 line:95%,end
Here we go.

00:15:49.949 --> 00:15:53.352 line:95%,end
Maddie is the center
of the group choreography.

00:15:53.419 --> 00:15:57.189 line:95%,end
And without her here it's really difficult
to go on with this routine.

00:15:58.557 --> 00:16:00.025 line:95%,end
MELISSA: <i>I really didn't</i>
<i>want to go to the studio,</i>

00:16:00.092 --> 00:16:03.529 line:5%,start
but I finally thought I need to
drop my kids off at rehearsal.

00:16:03.595 --> 00:16:05.464 line:95%,end
I really don't have to be there
when they practice.

00:16:06.131 --> 00:16:07.433 line:95%,end
ABBY: Get in here! Let's go!

00:16:09.468 --> 00:16:10.536 line:95%,end
-HOLLY: Maddie arrived.
-CHRISTI: Oh, good.

00:16:10.602 --> 00:16:12.171 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Look at the timing. She's here.

00:16:12.237 --> 00:16:14.173 line:95%,end
Good. So then we--
our kids don't have to bear

00:16:14.239 --> 00:16:15.541 line:95%,end
the brunt of this one's anger.

00:16:15.607 --> 00:16:18.911 line:95%,end
Hey. I never want this to happen, again.

00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:21.013 line:95%,end
You're in a group dance.
You're part of the team.

00:16:21.080 --> 00:16:22.581 line:95%,end
You do not miss rehearsal.

00:16:22.648 --> 00:16:23.849 line:95%,end
This whole thing with your mother--

00:16:23.916 --> 00:16:25.317 line:95%,end
forget about it.

00:16:25.384 --> 00:16:26.685 line:95%,end
You're going to--look up there.

00:16:26.752 --> 00:16:29.555 line:95%,end
You're going to let those women
dictate your future?

00:16:29.621 --> 00:16:30.956 line:95%,end
That's crazy.

00:16:31.023 --> 00:16:34.660 line:95%,end
I cannot believe
how much time we have lost

00:16:34.727 --> 00:16:35.961 line:95%,end
because of Melissa.

00:16:36.028 --> 00:16:38.130 line:95%,end
Run, run! Up! Go!

00:16:38.197 --> 00:16:41.967 line:95%,end
We've got to dig down deep inside
and use everything we've got

00:16:42.034 --> 00:16:44.303 line:95%,end
if we're going to win
this weekend at Starbound.

00:16:44.370 --> 00:16:46.538 line:95%,end
Girls, we have two more days--

00:16:46.605 --> 00:16:49.875 line:95%,end
two more days to get this number clean.

00:16:49.942 --> 00:16:51.710 line:95%,end
-You understand?
-Yes.

00:16:51.777 --> 00:16:53.979 line:95%,end
-ABBY: All right, go.
-Thank you.


00:16:56.949 --> 00:16:59.685 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:17:03.489 --> 00:17:05.858 line:95%,end
Thank you for calling
and tipping me off, though.

00:17:05.924 --> 00:17:08.260 line:95%,end
I appreciate my friends in this business.

00:17:08.327 --> 00:17:09.661 line:95%,end
Thanks. Bye-bye.

00:17:09.728 --> 00:17:14.066 line:5%,start
so, lo and behold, I find out that Cathy

00:17:14.133 --> 00:17:18.404 line:95%,end
and her rotten apples
are going to be joining us this weekend.

00:17:18.470 --> 00:17:22.641 line:95%,end
<i>Cathy has entered a routine</i>
<i>in each one of our categories.</i>

00:17:22.708 --> 00:17:24.610 line:95%,end
She's obviously out for revenge.

00:17:24.676 --> 00:17:28.380 line:95%,end
Justice is in a duet

00:17:28.447 --> 00:17:29.515 line:95%,end
with another little boy.

00:17:29.581 --> 00:17:30.949 line:95%,end
They don't have another boy.

00:17:31.016 --> 00:17:32.618 line:95%,end
This just gets better and better.

00:17:32.684 --> 00:17:35.754 line:95%,end
Cathy's bringing in a ringer
to dance with Justice

00:17:35.821 --> 00:17:37.556 line:95%,end
and go up against my duet.

00:17:37.623 --> 00:17:40.092 line:95%,end
Maddie can be Justice.
She's beat him before.

00:17:40.159 --> 00:17:42.261 line:95%,end
-She has to do a solo.
-She has to do a solo.

00:17:42.327 --> 00:17:44.797 line:95%,end
I know I told Maddie
she didn't get a solo this week.

00:17:44.863 --> 00:17:48.300 line:95%,end
But now I want her
to go up against Justice,

00:17:48.367 --> 00:17:49.902 line:95%,end
just to intimidate him.

00:17:49.968 --> 00:17:51.170 line:95%,end
Hi, babe. How are you?

00:17:51.236 --> 00:17:52.404 line:95%,end
-I'm good.
-Hi, Ab.

00:17:52.471 --> 00:17:54.673 line:95%,end
ABBY: Hey, Kenz.

00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:57.209 line:95%,end
You girls go ahead and get ready.
I want to talk to you for a second.

00:17:57.276 --> 00:18:01.780 line:95%,end
Melissa waltzes into the studio
like nothing happened yesterday.

00:18:01.847 --> 00:18:05.250 line:95%,end
At the very least, I think that woman
owes me an explanation.

00:18:05.317 --> 00:18:07.119 line:95%,end
I need to know where, were you yesterday

00:18:07.186 --> 00:18:08.320 line:95%,end
and why the girls weren't here.

00:18:08.387 --> 00:18:10.222 line:95%,end
I was not here. I don't have to be here.

00:18:10.289 --> 00:18:12.257 line:5%,start
I know Abby's upset,
but I don't need to be here

00:18:12.324 --> 00:18:13.692 line:5%,start
when my kids are dancing.

00:18:13.759 --> 00:18:15.894 line:95%,end
And I'm just sick of being
bullied by the moms.

00:18:15.961 --> 00:18:18.464 line:95%,end
My kids take care of themselves,
and they're here on time.

00:18:18.530 --> 00:18:19.765 line:95%,end
-So I'm not playing games.
-Okay.

00:18:19.832 --> 00:18:22.234 line:95%,end
Well, I'm not playing games, either.
Maddie's doing a solo this weekend.

00:18:22.301 --> 00:18:24.103 line:95%,end
Yes, she is.
You signed a contract with me.

00:18:24.169 --> 00:18:26.405 line:95%,end
Abby just needs to know giving
my daughter a solo

00:18:26.472 --> 00:18:29.141 line:95%,end
<i>the night before a competition</i>
<i>is just too much pressure.</i>

00:18:29.208 --> 00:18:31.243 line:95%,end
